    "We therefore show how clinical data can be utilized for early AD prediction and identification of personalized biological hypotheses.",
    "Neurodegenerative disorders are devastating, heterogeneous and challenging to diagnose, and their burden in aging populations is expected t o continue to grow 1.",
    "Among these, AD is the most common form of dementia after age 65, and its hallmark memory loss and other cognitive symptoms are costly and onerous to both patients and caregivers.",
